oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: Lebanon Flood
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: View of a flood in Lebanon. People are swimming on the street. Several people are gathered around a monument in the center of the square near a monument. Stores in the background include N. N. Cook Hardware, Commerce Union Bank, and a shoe store. A street light with globes is in the foreground. Same as image DB# 30300.
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:source: Looking Back at Tennessee Photograph Collection, 1890-1981
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:subject: Floods; Stores & shops; Streets; People; Monuments; Banks; Swimming
